The paper deals with the computation of planar maxima and convex hull, which are classic problems in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The use of multisets and the consideration of input order and structure also suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the design and analysis of algorithms, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric concepts and properties, which suggests cs.GC (Geometric Computation) as a possible sub-category.
